com.io7m.jtensors.parameterized

Class PVectorI3L<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.io7m.jtensors.parameterized.PVectorI3L<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - A phantom type parameter.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    PVectorReadable2LType<T>, PVectorReadable3LType<T>, VectorReadable2LType, VectorReadable3LType

    @Immutable
public final class PVectorI3L<T>
extends Object
implements PVectorReadable3LType<T>

    A three-dimensional immutable vector type with integer elements.

    Values of this type are immutable and can therefore be safely accessed from multiple threads.

    Since:
    7.0.0

      • interpolateLinear

        public static <T> PVectorI3L<T> interpolateLinear(PVectorReadable3LType<T> v0,
                                                  PVectorReadable3LType<T> v1,
                                                  double alpha)
                                           throws ArithmeticException
        Linearly interpolate between v0 and v1 by the amount alpha. The alpha parameter controls the degree of interpolation, such that:
        • interpolateLinear(v0, v1, 0.0, r) → r = v0
        • interpolateLinear(v0, v1, 1.0, r) → r = v1
        Type Parameters:
        T - A phantom type parameter.
        Parameters:
        v0 - The left input vector.
        v1 - The right input vector.
        alpha - The interpolation value, between 0.0 and 1.0.
        Returns:
        (1 - alpha) * v0 + alpha * v1
        Throws:
        ArithmeticException - Iff an internal arithmetic operation causes an integer overflow.
        Since:
        7.0.0

      • projection

        public static <T> PVectorI3L<T> projection(PVectorReadable3LType<T> p,
                                           PVectorReadable3LType<T> q)
                                    throws ArithmeticException
        Calculate the projection of the vector p onto the vector q.
        Type Parameters:
        T - A phantom type parameter.
        Parameters:
        p - The left vector
        q - The right vector
        Returns:
        ((dotProduct p q) / magnitudeSquared q) * q
        Throws:
        ArithmeticException - Iff an internal arithmetic operation causes an integer overflow
        Since:
        7.0.0
